Credit Scoring

Loan default can be defined as the inability of a borrower to fulfill his or her loan obligation as at when due Default loans cost a lot on a bank on the way of its progress. It- Diminishes Asset Quality, Increases the Cost of Funds, Decreases the Profitability of the Bank, Decreases the Overall Credit Rating of the Bank

#Weight of Evidence (WOE) & Invormation Value (IV) ##WOE will shows predictive power of an independent variable in relation to dependent variable ## Information Value helps to select variables by using their order of importance

Credit_Scoring$flag_kredit_macet<-as.numeric(ifelse(Credit_Scoring$flag_kredit_macet == "Good", 0, 1))
IV <- Information::create_infotables(data=Credit_Scoring, NULL, y="flag_kredit_macet", 10)
IV$Summary$IV <- round(IV$Summary$IV*100,2)

sample <-sample(c(TRUE, FALSE), nrow(data_ROSE), replace = T, prob = c(0.7,0.3))
train_rose <- data_ROSE [sample,]
test_rose <- data_ROSE[!sample,]


M3 <- ksvm(flag_kredit_macet ~ ., data = train_rose, kernel = "vanilladot")
##  Setting default kernel parameters
M3_pred <- predict(M3, test_rose [,1:18], type="response")
head(M3_pred)
## [1] 0 0 0 1 0 1
## Levels: 0 1
M3_score <- predict(M3, test_rose, type = "decision")
M3_pred <- prediction (M3_score, test_rose$flag_kredit_macet)


M3_perf <- performance(M3_pred, measure = "tpr", x.measure = "fpr")
plot(M3_perf, colorize=TRUE, lwd=2, main="M3 SVM:Plot ROC curve - Vanilladot")
lines(x=c(0, 1), y=c(0, 1), col="red", lwd=1, lty=3);
lines(x=c(1, 0), y=c(0, 1), col="green", lwd=1, lty=4)

# Plot precision/recall curve
M3_perf_precision <- performance(M3_pred, measure = "prec", x.measure = "rec")
plot(M3_perf_precision, main="M3 SVM:Plot precision/recall curve")

# Plot accuracy as function of threshold
M3_perf_acc <- performance(M3_pred, measure = "acc")
plot(M3_perf_acc, main="M3 SVM:Plot accuracy as function of threshold")

# Model Performance

#KS & AUC M3
M3_AUROC <- round(performance(M3_pred, measure = "auc")@y.values[[1]]*100, 2)
M3_KS <- round(max(attr(M3_perf,'y.values')[[1]]-attr(M3_perf,'x.values')[[1]])*100, 2)
M3_Gini <- (2*M3_AUROC - 100)
cat("AUROC: ",M3_AUROC,"\tKS: ", M3_KS, "\tGini:", M3_Gini, "\n")
## AUROC:  68.4     KS:  26.58  Gini: 36.8
